Xue Feng served all but ten months of his eight year sentence at Beijing's No. 2 Prison .
He was detained in November 2007 and sentenced in 2010 on charges of 'illegally procuring state secrets'
The 50-year-old was the only American serving a sentence in a Chinese prison for the crime of endangering state security .
President Obama personally lobbied for his release during a visit to Beijing in November 2009 .